      <p>This customization creates a TEI schema with the bare minimum of tags
        to make a recognizable document, which can then be made
	unrecognisable by addition of word-level linguistic
	analysis. 
      </p>
<div><head>Basic text structure</head>

<p>In this very simple schema, a document contains just a
<gi>body</gi>, though this may be subdivided using nested <gi>div</gi>
elements. Within the <gi>div</gi> elements only <gi>head</gi> and
<gi>p</gi> elements are permitted. 
<specList>
<specDesc key="div"/>
<specDesc key="head"/>
<specDesc key="p"/>
</specList>
</p>
<p>The <gi>head</gi> and <gi>p</gi> elements have the same structure:
they must contain at least one <gi>s</gi> element, representing a
sentence-like unit. The <gi>s</gi> element can contain any number of
<gi>w</gi> or <gi>pc</gi> elements, representing lexical and
punctuation tokens respectively. To make formatting easier, white
space is also permitted within <gi>s</gi> elements.</p>

<p>The following specification group deletes all the unwanted
